The reaction of $$\mathrm{KMnO}_{4}$$ with $$\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{2}$$ in acidic medium is as
<br/><br/>
$$
\begin{aligned}
2 \mathrm{KMnO}_{4}+3 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}+5 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{2} \\
& \rightarrow \mathrm{K}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}+2 \mathrm{MnSO}_{4}+8 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}+5 \mathrm{O}_{2}
\end{aligned}
$$<br/><br/>
$$\therefore \mathrm{Mn}^{2+}$$ will be formed as the product.
